HEADWORD: Preconcert
<hw>Pre`con*cert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Preconcerted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Preconcerting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To concert or arrange
beforehand; to settle by previous agreement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

